UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1307
1 calculus, chemistry, computer science, environmental science, and physics, and
2 International Baccalaureate or IB biology, chemistry, computer science,
3 environmental systems, mathematical studies, further mathematics, and physics;[.]
4 (3) "Board" means the Kentucky Board of Education;[.]
5 (4) "College Board Advanced Placement examination" means the advanced placement
6 test administered by the College Entrance Examination Board;[.]
7 (5) "College Board" means the College Entrance Examination Board, a national
8 nonprofit association that provides college admission guidance and advanced
9 placement examinations;[.]
10 (6) "Core curriculum" means at least one (1) course in science, one (1) course in
11 mathematics, and at least one (1) course in two (2) of the following subject areas:
12 English, social studies, foreign language, and the arts;[.]
13 (7) "Department" means the Kentucky Department of Education;[.]
14 (8) "Dual credit" means a college-level course of study developed in accordance with
15 KRS 164.098 in which a high school student receives credit from both the high
16 school and postsecondary institution in which the student is enrolled upon
17 completion of a single class or designated program of study;[.]
18 (9) "Dual enrollment" means a college-level course of study developed in accordance
19 with KRS 164.098 in which a student is enrolled in a high school and
20 postsecondary institution simultaneously;[.]
21 (10) "International Baccalaureate" or "IB" means the International Baccalaureate
22 Organization's Diploma Programme, a comprehensive two (2) year program
23 designed for highly motivated students;[.]
24 (11) "Kentucky Virtual High School" means secondary-level instructional programs or
25 courses offered by the Kentucky Department of Education through the Internet and
26 other on-line, computer-based methods;[.]
27 (12) "Kentucky Virtual University" means a college-level instructional program offered
Page 5 of 6
