UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1307
1 by the Council on Postsecondary Education through the Internet or other on-line,
2 computer-based methods; and[.]
3 (13) "Menstrual product" means a tampon, panty liner, menstrual cup, pad, or any
4 other similar tangible personal property designed for use in connection with the
5 human menstrual cycle, but does not include any items of clothing or "grooming
6 and hygiene products" as defined in KRS 139.472.
7 Section 5. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
8 $2,000,000 in each fiscal year of the 2026-2028 fiscal biennium to the Learning and
9 Results Services budget unit within the Department of Education to provide menstrual
10 products for students, as set forth in Sections 1 to 4 of this Act.
11 Section 6. Whereas providing timely funding for the access and provision of
12 menstrual products in schools in the Commonwealth is important for the citizens of this
13 state, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect July 1, 2026.
